RENT AGREEMENT / LEASE DEED

This Rent Agreement ("Agreement") is made and executed on this [Day] day of [Month], [Year] at [City/Place].

BETWEEN

[LANDLORD'S FULL NAME], Son/Daughter/Wife of [Landlord's Father's/Husband's Name], aged [Age], residing at [Landlord's Full Address] (hereinafter referred to as the "LANDLORD" or "LESSOR", which expression shall unless repugnant to the context or meaning thereof mean and include his/her heirs, successors, legal representatives, administrators, executors, and assigns) of the FIRST PART.

AND

[TENANT'S FULL NAME], Son/Daughter/Wife of [Tenant's Father's/Husband's Name], aged [Age], residing at [Tenant's Current Address, if different, otherwise mention Permanent Address] (hereinafter referred to as the "TENANT" or "LESSEE", which expression shall unless repugnant to the context or meaning thereof mean and include his/her heirs, successors, legal representatives, administrators, executors, and assigns) of the SECOND PART.

WHEREAS the Landlord is the absolute owner and is in possession of the property bearing No. [Full Address of the Rented Property], consisting of [Brief Description, e.g., 2 Bedrooms, 1 Hall, 1 Kitchen, 2 Bathrooms] (hereinafter referred to as the "DEMISED PREMISES").

WHEREAS the Tenant has approached the Landlord to take the Demised Premises on rent for residential purposes, and the Landlord has agreed to let out the Demised Premises to the Tenant on the following terms and conditions:

NOW THIS AGREEMENT WITNESSETH AS FOLLOWS:

1.  TERM: This Agreement shall be for a period of [Number, e.g., 11] months, commencing from [Start Date, e.g., DD/MM/YYYY] and ending on [End Date, e.g., DD/MM/YYYY]. This term may be renewed for a further period upon mutual consent of both parties, with revised terms and rent as may be agreed upon.

2.  RENT: The Tenant shall pay the Landlord a monthly rent of Rs. [Amount]/- (Rupees [Amount in Words] only). The rent shall be paid in advance on or before the [Day, e.g., 5th] day of each English calendar month, by [Payment Method, e.g., Bank Transfer to Account No. XXXXX, Cash].

3.  SECURITY DEPOSIT: The Tenant has paid a sum of Rs. [Amount]/- (Rupees [Amount in Words] only) as an interest-free refundable security deposit to the Landlord. The Landlord shall refund this amount to the Tenant upon expiry of the lease term and vacation of the premises, subject to deductions for any unpaid rent, damages to the property (excluding normal wear and tear), and unpaid utility bills.

4.  USE OF PREMISES: The Demised Premises shall be used by the Tenant solely for [Residential / Commercial] purposes for himself/herself and his/her family members only and not for any illegal or immoral activities.

5.  UTILITIES: The Tenant shall pay for all utility charges including electricity, water, cooking gas, internet, cable TV, etc., consumed during the tenancy period directly to the concerned authorities based on actual usage/bills. The Landlord shall bear the property taxes.

6.  MAINTENANCE: The Tenant shall maintain the Demised Premises in good and habitable condition and shall be responsible for minor repairs. Major structural repairs shall be the responsibility of the Landlord, unless caused by the Tenant's negligence.

7.  INSPECTION: The Landlord or his/her authorized representative shall have the right to enter and inspect the Demised Premises at reasonable times with prior notice to the Tenant.

8.  SUBLETTING: The Tenant shall not sublet, assign, or part with the possession of the Demised Premises or any part thereof without the prior written consent of the Landlord.

9.  ALTERATIONS: The Tenant shall not make any structural additions or alterations to the Demised Premises without the prior written consent of the Landlord.

10. TERMINATION: Either party may terminate this Agreement by giving [Number, e.g., One] month's written notice to the other party.

11. VACATION: Upon expiry or termination of this Agreement, the Tenant shall peacefully vacate and hand over the vacant possession of the Demised Premises to the Landlord in the same condition as received, subject to normal wear and tear.

12. GOVERNING LAW: This Agreement shall be governed by the laws of India, and the courts at [City/Jurisdiction] shall have exclusive jurisdiction.

IN WITNESS WHEREOF, the parties hereto have signed this Agreement on the day, month, and year first above written.


